1
00:00:02,114 --> 00:00:06,954
Really, your first connection,
substantially, with Reality

2
00:00:06,954 --> 00:00:11,262
is hearing from an agent,
a divine agent.

3
00:00:11,355 --> 00:00:15,960
sthāne sthitāḥ śruti-gatāḿ
tanu-vāṅ-manobhir

4
00:00:16,207 --> 00:00:20,278
[Skull Size Kingdom vs. The Infinite]

5
00:00:20,984 --> 00:00:24,569
jñāne prayāsam udapāsya namanta eva
[SB: 10.14.3]

6
00:00:24,569 --> 00:00:29,522
Give up trying to understand Him

7
00:00:29,522 --> 00:00:32,974
with your intellect and your brain—

8
00:00:33,313 --> 00:00:34,508
the Infinite.

9
00:00:34,508 --> 00:00:37,905
Or what the writer
David Foster Wallace called,

10
00:00:37,905 --> 00:00:45,431
“We consider ourselves the lords
of our own skull-sized kingdoms.”

11
00:00:45,582 --> 00:00:47,956
He put that nicely.

12
00:00:47,956 --> 00:00:51,455
Saraswatī Ṭhākur told,
“Puppy brain”—

13
00:00:51,534 --> 00:00:54,037
trying to conceive the Infinite
in that way.

14
00:00:54,037 --> 00:00:55,875
But, the Infinite ...

15
00:00:55,875 --> 00:00:58,536
Guru Mahārāj brings
the good news to us,

16
00:00:58,536 --> 00:01:03,111
“The Infinite can make Itself 
known to the finite,

17
00:01:03,534 --> 00:01:06,210
if He chooses.”

18
00:01:06,683 --> 00:01:16,900
tasyaiṣa ātmā vivṛṇute tanūḿ svām

19
00:01:16,900 --> 00:01:20,804
The Upanishads:
nāyam ātmā pravachanena labhya

20
00:01:20,804 --> 00:01:23,890
na medhayā na bahunā śrutena
[Ku: 3.2.23]

21
00:01:23,890 --> 00:01:26,319
Not by so much discussion,

22
00:01:26,319 --> 00:01:29,395
not by mere intellect,

23
00:01:29,395 --> 00:01:34,226
but He reveals Himself
to whom He chooses

24
00:01:34,226 --> 00:01:37,692
through whom He chooses.

25
00:01:38,627 --> 00:01:43,284
And His favourite agency
for distribution

26
00:01:43,284 --> 00:01:45,876
is His devotee, agent.

27
00:01:47,364 --> 00:01:51,380
Whatever your position is, 
it’s irrelevant.

28
00:01:51,466 --> 00:01:54,481
And this is very beautiful
because people say,

29
00:01:54,481 --> 00:01:56,252
“What about this? 
What about that?

30
00:01:56,252 --> 00:01:57,467
What if someone lives like this?

31
00:01:57,467 --> 00:01:58,674
What if someone believes that?

32
00:01:58,674 --> 00:02:01,242
What if someone finds themselves
in this situation?

33
00:02:01,242 --> 00:02:03,462
What if circumstantially …?”

34
00:02:03,462 --> 00:02:05,375
What does it say,
“Sthāne sthitāḥ—

35
00:02:05,375 --> 00:02:09,435
whatever your situation is,

36
00:02:09,435 --> 00:02:16,288
begin hearing about Kṛṣṇa
from His agent:

37
00:02:16,867 --> 00:02:18,798
Sādhu, Śāstra, Guru, Vaiṣṇava,

38
00:02:18,798 --> 00:02:21,244
but particularly, the devotee.”

